Theapplicationofmasterylearning,wherestudentsprogressthrough theirlearninginaself-pacedmanneruntiltheyhavemasteredspe-cificconcepts,isconsideredappealingforteachingintroductory programmingcourses.Despiteitsgrowingpopularityincomputing anditsextensiveuseinotherdisciplines,thereisnooverviewof thedesignofcoursesthatusemasterylearning.Inthisposition paper,wepresentanoverviewoffivemasterylearningmodelsand discussexamplesofhowthesecanbeappliedinpractice,bothin foundationalprogrammingaswellasmoreadvancedcourses.Our analysisfocusesonthestudentprogressionthroughthecourse, theassessmentstructure,andthesupportforself-pacedlearning, includingforstrugglingstudents.Thisworkprovidesagreaterun-derstandingofmasterylearninganditsapplicationinacomputing educationcontext.